        ⊆
        g
      
    
    {\displaystyle p\subseteq g}
  , we find that 
  
    
      
        g
        (
        n
        )
      
    
    {\displaystyle g(n)}
   is defined.
Let 
  
    
      
        X
        =
        
          
            g
            
              −
              1
            
          
        
        [
        1
        ]
      
    
    {\displaystyle X={g^{-1}}[1]}
  , the set of all "yes" members of the generic conditions. It is possible to give a name for 
  
    
      
        X
      
    
    {\displaystyle X}
   directly. Let 

  
    
      
        
          
            X
            _
          
        
        =
        
          {
          
            
              (
              
                
                  
                    
                      n
                      ˇ
                    
                  
                
                ,
                p
              
