    {\displaystyle {\underline {X}}=\left\{\left({\check {n}},p\right)\mid p(n)=1\right\}.}
  Then 
  
    
      
        val
        ⁡
        (
        
          
            X
            _
          
        
        ,
        G
        )
        =
        X
        .
      
    
    {\displaystyle \operatorname {val} ({\underline {X}},G)=X.}
   Now suppose that 
  
    
      
        A
        ⊆
        ω
      
    
    {\displaystyle A\subseteq \omega }
   in 
  
    
      
        V
      
    
    {\displaystyle V}
  . We claim that 
  
    
      
        X
        ≠
        A
      
    
    {\displaystyle X\neq A}
  . Let 

  
    
      
        
          D
          
            A
          
        
        =
        {
        p
        ∣
        (
        ∃
        n
        )
        (
