    {\displaystyle C}
   also has the finite intersection property. Elements of the set 
  
    
      
        C
      
    
    {\displaystyle C}
   are bounded closed sets as closures of bounded sets. Therefore, 
  
    
      
        C
      
    
    {\displaystyle C}
  
