   proves that if a countable transitive model 
  
    
      
        M
      
    
    {\displaystyle M}
   satisfies 
  
    
      
        
          T
          ′
        
      
    
    {\displaystyle T'}
  , then 
  
    
      
        M
        [
        G
        ]
      
    
    {\displaystyle M[G]}
   satisfies 
  
    
      
        T
      
    
    {\displaystyle T}
  . By proving that there is finite set 
  
    
      
        
          T
          ″
        
      
    
    {\displaystyle T''}
   of 
  
    
      
        
          
            Z
            F
            C
          
        
      
    
    {\displaystyle {\mathsf {ZFC}}}
